  <TEXT> 
	 <BODY> 
		<DIV1 TYPE="letter"><PB N="[1]"> 
		  <OPENER> 
			 <ADDRESS> 
				<ADDRLINE>Knoxville 
				  <DATE VALUE="1797-06-08">8th day of June 1797</DATE></ADDRLINE> 
			 </ADDRESS> 
			 <SALUTE>Brothers</SALUTE></OPENER> 
		  <P>I have no doubt <DEL TYPE="overstrike">but</DEL> you have heard that
		  some disputes is likely to take place, <ORIG REG="though">tho</ORIG> I hope it
		  will not be the case, between 
		  <NAME TYPE="place">America</NAME> <DEL TYPE="overstrike">Us</DEL> and
		  some of the Nations over and beyond the Great Waters. Should Such a war take
		  place, I have reason to believe they will endeavor to cause the young Warriors
		  of your Nation <UNCLEAR>unk</UNCLEAR> more to lift the hatchet against your
		  brothers the 
		  <NAME TYPE="person"><ORIG REG="Americans">americans</ORIG></NAME>. I
		  take this opportunity my brothers to Warn you in time, that you may Watch over
		  your Young men, who is too apt to listen <PB N="[2]"> to talks of War, (I
		  <ORIG REG="don't">dont</ORIG> mean the young men of your Nation in particular)
		  but <DEL TYPE="overstrike">of</DEL> all other young men, as well as
		  <DEL TYPE="overstrike">those of</DEL> yours <DEL
		  TYPE="overstrike">Nation</DEL>, is too ready to listen to talks of this kind,
		  without considering the great injury it May do to the good people of their
		  nation, And the many poor women &amp; children that Always Suffers in
		  consequence of such events. </P> 
		  <P>None my friends Should any people whatever come or Send
			 <DEL TYPE="overstrike">in to</DEL> <ADD PLACE="supralinear">into</ADD> your
		  Nation requesting or encouraging your people to make war, against any of your 
		  <NAME TYPE="person">American</NAME> brothers, <ORIG
		  REG="don't">dont</ORIG> you listen to <DEL TYPE="overstrike">them</DEL> their
		  talks, but on the contrary hold your brothers fast by the hand, who is the only
		  people that can be your good friends, or <ADD PLACE="supralinear">your</ADD>
		  great enemies; we live Very <DEL TYPE="overstrike">Close</DEL> near to each
		  other and on the same land, And it is the wish of <ADD
		  PLACE="supralinear">all</ADD> the <ADD PLACE="supralinear">good</ADD> 
		  <NAME TYPE="person">Americans</NAME>, to live in peace and friendship
		  with <DEL TYPE="overstrike">all</DEL> <ADD PLACE="supralinear">you &amp;
		  all</ADD> their red brothers</P> 
		  <P REND="words missing from tex">The people over the big water
			 <ORIG REG="don't">dont</ORIG> care much <PB N="[3]"> about us people of 
			 <NAME TYPE="place">America</NAME>, and was we to go to war
			 <DEL TYPE="overstrike">Against each other</DEL> and kill and destroy each other
			 over so much, they would only laugh at us for it, and call us fools &mdash; I
			 hope you will listen well to my talks and think good of them in your hearts
			 &mdash; remember that I have always advised you to live in peace, with Your 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">American</NAME>brothers, and also all other
			 people, and your own good Sense will none tell you, it would have been best for
			 you to have lived in peace &mdash; You remember last war you was told by people
			 over the 
			 <NAME TYPE="place">Great Water</NAME>, that the 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">Americans</NAME> was like nothing that they would
			 all be killed &amp; drive away, but you have long seen <DEL
			 TYPE="overstrike">such</DEL> <ADD PLACE="supralinear">those</ADD> stories was
			 all false, you see the 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">Americans</NAME> is still here <LB> and as firm
			 as the mountains therefore I hope you will listen to <ADD
			 PLACE="supralinear">no</ADD>, more talks of such a kind</P> 
		  <CLOSER> 
			 <SALUTE>Your friend &amp; brother</SALUTE> 
			 <SIGNED> 
				<NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="John">J.</ABBR>
				  Sevier</NAME></SIGNED> 
			 <ADDRESS> 
				<ADDRLINE>Warriors &amp; Chiefs <LB> of the 
				  <NAME TYPE="place">Cherokee Nation</NAME> </ADDRLINE> 
			 </ADDRESS></CLOSER> 
		</DIV1> 
